The paper deals with the construction of locally correctable and locally testable codes, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS, cs.CC). The paper also involves the construction of codes with good distance properties, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and computational complexity, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
